# Cursor rules — Tomo repo

## Shared tree with Claude Code
A Claude Code session may be editing this same working tree in parallel.
Before any edit or git operation, run `git status` and `git diff --stat`
to see what's already in flight. Never run `git add -A` or `git add .` —
stage files by explicit path only. Never `git commit --amend`. Never
`git push origin main` without the user explicitly saying "push" in this
Cursor session (not in another tool).

## No concurrent git writers
If you see a non-empty working tree you didn't create, stop and ask the
user before modifying shared files. Prior incident: two agents + CLI git
hit `.git/index.lock` simultaneously and almost wiped 1,602 tracked
files. Check for `.git/index.lock` before any git op and refuse to
delete it without the user confirming no other process holds it.

## Dev servers
One Metro per machine. Port 8081 is owned by whichever tool started
Expo first. If `lsof -i :8081` shows another clone's node process, do
NOT run `expo start` — ask the user. If you need your own dev server,
use port 8082+. Never run `backend/scripts/deploy-frontend.sh` — that
bundles the whole working tree to production and is a Claude Code /
explicit-user-approval operation.

## Path discipline
Work only inside `/Users/tareqelkayyali/Desktop/Tomo/tomo-app`. If a
file path resolves to `~/Desktop/tomo-cursor/` or any other checkout,
stop and tell the user — you're in the wrong clone.

## Existing conventions
Read `CLAUDE.md` at repo root before starting. It carries the Tomo
project's commands, architecture map, and rules (Supabase ports,
readiness system, etc.). Follow the rules there as if they were
written for you.

## Chat UI work uses the new primitives
Any chat-surface edits must use the Tomo chat primitives under
`mobile/src/components/chat/tomo/` (UserBubble, TomoTitle, TomoBody,
TurnMark, MetricRow, Table, Suggestions, FormSection, RadioRow,
NumberChipRow, PillChipRow, CTA, Composer). Do not re-introduce the
old rounded-card chat style.

## No emojis, ever
No emojis anywhere: code, prompts, UI text, commit messages, comments.
Project-wide rule; the codebase has already been swept clean.

## Commit messages
Scoped prefix: `feat(area):`, `fix(area):`, `chore:`, `docs:`.
Subject under 70 chars, imperative. Body explains why, not what.
Co-author line is managed by Claude Code commits; Cursor commits
don't need one.